<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - TRANSMISSION TEMPERATURE GAUGE,
        SENDER, CIRCUITS AND CLUSTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TRANSMISSION TEMPERATURE GAUGE, SENDER, CIRCUITS AND CLUSTER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_8.xml" xrefid="x0824509">Rear Axle, Engine Oil and Transmission Oil
                    Temperature Gauges
                    <xref refid="x0824509"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for an operation description of the pyrometer system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transmission Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
            <para>This test will determine if the gauge is working. It does not determine if the gauge is reading
                accurately.
            </para>
            <table id="t0824522">
                <title>Transmission Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector. (N/L) circuit 31 at the transmission temperature sender.
                                    Does gauge read at or below low scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Transmission temperature sender, 31.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect sender circuit 31 and go to
                                    Transmission Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Use a test lead to jumper sender circuit 31 to ground. Does the gauge read above
                                    high scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Transmission temperature sender, 31 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit and cluster test good. Reconnect sender. Go to Transmission Temperature
                                    Gauge and Sender Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect sender circuit 31 and go to
                                    Transmission Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transmission Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Transmission Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test prior to performing this test.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824523">
                <title>Transmission Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (284) or sender and ground wire from transmission temperature
                                    sender. Measure resistance to ground at 31-G.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(284) or ground wire, 31-G to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 31-G/11-GU for Cummins N14 or Detroit
                                    Diesel engines; or 31-G/11-GJ in Cummins M11 or ISM engines, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove connector (72) from the gauge cluster. At connector (72) measure resistance
                                    to ground at circuit 31B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 31B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 31B/31A connector (102)/(338), or circuit 31A,
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At sender connector (284) or sender and ground wires use test lead to jumper
                                    circuit 31A to 31-G. At connector (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 31B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 31B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 31B/31A, connector (102)/(338), or
                                    circuit 31A, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove transmission temperature gauge. Measure resistance between cluster
                                    connector (72) cavity 2 and the gauge ground pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 2 to ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (72) cavity 6, and the gauge ignition
                                    pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 6 to ignition pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (72) cavity 10, and the gauge sender
                                    pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 10 to sender pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Reconnect (72) and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Turn key on. Measure voltage at axle gauge ignition pin to ground, to check
                                    circuit 28A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28A/13D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure voltage between gauge ignition and ground pins, to check circuit
                                    11-GW/11-GD.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit checks good, Re-install gauge and go to Transmission Temperature Gauge and
                                    Sender Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GW/11-GD, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transmission Temperature Gauge and Sender Test</title>
            <table id="t0824524">
                <title>Transmission Temperature Gauge and Sender Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.23in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect gauge tester ZTSE-2781
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824516">(Figure 16)</hotlnk>
                                    and
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824517">(Figure 17)</hotlnk>
                                    to connector (284) or sender wire at sender unit, circuit 31A and ground. Set to 108
                                    Ohms. Does transmission temperature gauge read 220&#176;F (104.4&#176;C)?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>284) or sender wire, 31A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>108 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With gauge tester still connected, set to 35 ohms. Does transmission temperature
                                    gauge read 320&#176;F (160&#176;C)?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(284) or sender wire, 31A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>35 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge and circuits check good. Replace sender.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
